FT  02 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Thames Water Dollars 500m deal
Thames Water has clinched a Dollars 500m (Pounds 342m) deal to develop water
and waste infrastructure in Mexico City as part of a consortium with two
Mexican companies.
Thames is expected to invest a total of about Dollars 50m in the joint
venture, which has won a 15 year concession for the municipality of
Naucalpan. The first phase will require investment of about Dollars 15m.
The UK water company will have a 45 per cent stake, along with Tribasa, a
Mexican civil engineering group, while Epycsa, a specialist water
contractor, will own 10 per cent.
